evidenced_summary.user_template:
PAPER DIRECTIVES (exact text from paper):
{directives_exact_text}

PAPER IMPACT: percent={impact_percent}, absolute={impact_absolute}; evidence quote: {impact_evidence}

TRIAL: NCT {trial_instance_id}, enrollment={enrollment}

MATCH QUOTES: directive: {change_directive_quote}
rationale: {change_rationale_quote}

GAINS: paper_pct_gain={paper_pct_gain} (percent increase from paper), scalar_gain={scalar_gain} (estimated additional patients = enrollment × paper_pct_gain/100).

Write a short evidenced summary: (1) How ECs are amended (use the directive and rationale quotes); (2) How accrual is computed (use the impact evidence quote; describe scalar_gain as estimated additional patients, not post-amendment enrollment). Plain text, one or two paragraphs.

directives.user_template:
Title: {title}

Abstract (or supplied text):
{abstract}

Does the paper confidently have exact directives for how eligibility criteria should be changed? If so, can you tell me exactly the things to change given the information already present? If not, does the paper indicate that the information for exact directives exists within the paper (not the present information such as the abstract)?

Respond with JSON only, e.g.: {{"answer_location": "exact", "directives_exact_text": "...", "directives_count": 2}} or {{"answer_location": "in_paper", "directives_exact_text": null, "directives_count": null}} or {{"answer_location": "none", "directives_exact_text": null, "directives_count": null}}.

impact.user_template:
Title: {title}

Abstract (or supplied text):
{abstract}

Does the paper quantify the *change* in eligible patients or enrollment from broadening/amending eligibility criteria? If yes, extract: (1) impact_percent = the percent *increase* (e.g. 100 for doubling, 50 for 50% more), not the share who are eligible; (2) impact_absolute = the additional number of patients/participants, if given; (3) impact_evidence = the exact verbatim quote from the paper that supports these numbers (for justification). If the paper only gives proportions (e.g. "98% eligible") without a clear increase, prefer impact_absolute or impact_qualitative. If not present, say so.

Respond with JSON only, e.g.: {{"answer_location": "exact", "impact_percent": 100, "impact_absolute": 4851, "impact_unit": "percent", "impact_qualitative": null, "impact_evidence": "..."}} or {{"answer_location": "none", ...}}.
